{# Evaluation prompt for comparing three answers to one question #}
You will evaluate three Korean answers to the same question grounded in a text-centric image.

Criteria (score 1-7):
- Utility: Does the answer fully address the question with useful detail?
- Accuracy: Aligned with the image text; no external knowledge.
- Context fit: Respects constraints (no tables/charts; stays in textual body).
- Format: Markdown rules (bolding, hyphens) applied when appropriate.

Instructions:
- Provide a short justification per answer.
- Select the best answer (highest score; break ties by utility then accuracy).
- Flag any policy violations (table/chart references, external info).

Output schema:
- scores: list of 3 integers (1-7)
- best_index: 0-based index of best answer
- notes: brief justification
- violations: list of strings (if any)
